{"id": "361185", "revid": "49723770", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=361185", "title": "The Darnassus Mission", "text": "Objectives.\nLocate the Divine Bell.\nYou may use the Silvermoon Charm to return to Fanlyr if you get in trouble.\nDescription.\nThe &lt;a href=\"%3ADivine%20Bell\"&gt;:Divine Bell&lt;/a&gt; is in the city. We don't want to cause a scene, we just want the artifact. I need you to find a way in, WITHOUT getting caught. That means no mounts, no flying, no fighting.\nI can provide aid. I will magically cloak you, so you may move with stealth. I will also give you a small charm that you may use to return to safety, should you get in trouble.\nNow go, &lt;name&gt;. Go, locate the bell, and tag it to be teleported back with you.\nRewards.\nYou will receive:\nProgress.\nThe bell, &lt;name&gt;!\nCompletion.\nWell executed, &lt;race&gt;! I knew we could count on you.\nNow to get off this wretched tree.\nNotes.\nPlayers receive a 30 minute buff - Darnassus Invader - that grants stealth in order to travel through Darnassus. They also receive an ability button - Sunreavers' Portal-Charm - that can be used, with a 60 second cooldown, if they lose their buff.\nPlayers will lose their stealth buff by engaging in combat, using any abilities, being detected by the guards, and riding a mount.\nWarning! You will have to navigate through the actual, main-world Darnassus, not an instanced or phased version. You will see any Alliance players that happen to be there, and if you drop out of stealth, they will see you too \u2014 with predictable results, as you are PvP flagged.\nThe Bell is in an underground cave in the west of the &lt;a href=\"Cenarion%20Enclave\"&gt;Cenarion Enclave&lt;/a&gt;, roughly to the south of the letter \"i\" in \"Cenarion Enclave\" at the end of the road leading west. The safest route probably is:\nAlternatively, you can swim through the water to avoid the Sentinels. If you want to use water-walking abilities, cast them beforehand, as casting them while stealthed will break stealth.\nSince \"&lt;a href=\"Battle%20for%20Azeroth\"&gt;Battle for Azeroth&lt;/a&gt;\", if you attempt to do this quest with a level 110+ character, you will get ported to Darkshore instead of Darnassus, since Darnassus is destroyed in the default phase. You can talk to &lt;a href=\"Zidormi\"&gt;Zidormi&lt;/a&gt; in Darkshore to return to the past, where Darnassus is reachable, which will allow you to get there and complete the quest."}
