{"id": "186951", "revid": "39381941", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=186951", "title": "The Dead Mines (WC1 Human)", "text": "The Dead Mines is the fourth mission of the &lt;a href=\"Human\"&gt;Human&lt;/a&gt; campaign in \"\".\nMission briefing.\n\"It has been some twenty months since Sir &lt;a href=\"Anduin%20Lothar\"&gt;Lothar&lt;/a&gt;, one of the crown's greatest heroes, led an expedition into the &lt;a href=\"Deadmines\"&gt;Dead Mines&lt;/a&gt; to search for the Lost &lt;a href=\"%3ATome%20of%20Divinity\"&gt;:Tome of Divinity&lt;/a&gt;. They were never heard from again. However, the great knight has recently appeared to the &lt;a href=\"Abbot%20of%20Northshire%20Abbey\"&gt;Abbot of Northshire&lt;/a&gt; in a vision - battered and pleading for assistance. &lt;a href=\"Llane%20Wrynn%20I\"&gt;King Llane&lt;/a&gt; has ordered &lt;a href=\"Defender%20of%20the%20Crown\"&gt;you&lt;/a&gt; to lead a detachment of warriors and healers into the mines in an attempt to find Sir Lothar, heal him, and bring him and any other survivors back alive.\"\nGuide.\nThis mission will take a little while. The enemy forces greatly outnumber yours, so rushing it may result in considerable casualties. You do have access to Clerics and healing, so be sure to top off your units' health and keep them alive. The safest way to handle this mission is to keep a tight formation with your Footmen at the front of your forces, your Archers behind them, and your Clerics in the rear. Keep an opening for an Archer to retreat back to your forces, so that it does not get trapped out in the open where he can be killed by an Ogre.\nSend an Archer ahead to scout the caves. Have him frequently stop to get optimum vision and to watch for incoming Ogres; they will be regularly sent against your forces. When you see one approaching, bring your Archer back to your other forces (They will outrun them) and select a Cleric so he can heal as needed. Once a good chunk of the path looks clear, move your forces forward and set up their formation, once more. Players will be doing this until reach a large room near the end where several Ogres await them. Keep a tight formation after entering and explore the entire room with a single scout, luring Ogres over to your main attack force. After going into the next large room on the east side, you will find several neutral units covered in blankets along the northeast side. These are Lothar and his Archer companions. Once the area is clear, you can safely bring a unit over to rescue them. \nThere are four path branches along the caves, two of them contain Ogres.\nIf you see a branch, send an Archer in one direction to scout and lure Ogres back to the player. Once they are all defeated, you can safely advance your forces along the main path.\nOgre vs Footman&lt;br&gt;The two units share the same movement speed, but the Ogre has 1 more point of armor and their DPS (10.4 vs 7) far exceeds the Footman, making them the superior unit."}
