{"id": "463777", "revid": "49740203", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=463777", "title": "The Dead and the Damned (Alliance)", "text": "Objectives.\nTravel to &lt;a href=\"Dalaran\"&gt;Dalaran&lt;/a&gt; and fly upon &lt;a href=\"Zeomus\"&gt;Zeomus&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Darkstone%20Isle\"&gt;Darkstone Isle&lt;/a&gt;. While there, travel through the Demon Portal, find &lt;a href=\"Baron%20Sliver\"&gt;Baron Sliver&lt;/a&gt;, and obtain the &lt;a href=\"Maw%20of%20the%20Damned\"&gt;Maw of the Damned&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\n&lt;A powerful mind again touches your thoughts.&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Gorelix%20the%20Fleshripper\"&gt;Gorelix the Fleshripper&lt;/a&gt; is a monstrous demon. The butcher of a thousand worlds, he has exterminated countless races with his axe, the Maw of the Damned.\nA group of &lt;a href=\"Knights%20of%20the%20Ebon%20Blade\"&gt;Ebon Blade&lt;/a&gt; was dispatched to slay him but they have gone missing. You will succeed where they failed.\nYou will not be alone in this, I've sent Baron Sliver ahead to assist you.\nGo, obtain the Maw of the Damned and ensure that Gorelix is no more.\nCompletion.\nThat axe makes me feel uneasy, &lt;name&gt;. Its power is undeniable, but its very essence embodies the &lt;a href=\"eternal%20hunger\"&gt;eternal hunger&lt;/a&gt;.\nWe will use it because we must do whatever it takes to win this war. Still, I'd be careful with that weapon if I were you.\nNotes.\nUpon mounting Zeomus, you are transported to &lt;a href=\"Darkstone%20Isle\"&gt;Darkstone Isle&lt;/a&gt; on the western side of the Broken Shore where several Knights of the Ebon Blade are stationed. &lt;a href=\"Vanessa%20Fairgraves\"&gt;Vanessa Fairgraves&lt;/a&gt; is standing nearby and salutes you as you walk past.\n&lt;a href=\"Rantuko%20Grimtouch\"&gt;Rantuko Grimtouch&lt;/a&gt; is standing in front of the demon portal.\nUpon walking through the portal, you are transported to &lt;a href=\"Niskara\"&gt;Niskara&lt;/a&gt;.\nStage 1: Hunting the Hunters.\nSliver is found just up the path, having been shackled by a .\nUpon killing the jailer, Sliver is freed.\nStage 2: Scout the Path.\nKill the two and then proceed east.\nStage 3: Breaching the Defenses.\nA Felguard Sentry and emerge from a building to the north. Kill them both to proceed to the next stage.\nStage 4: The Search Continues.\nFollow Sliver east into the Legion camp and kill the Felguard Sentries patrolling the path.\nInside one of the buildings, &lt;a href=\"Dagnar%20Stonebrow\"&gt;Dagnar Stonebrow&lt;/a&gt; has been strung up with fel shackles.\nStage 5: End of the Inquisition.\nZalinor is found to the northeast overlooking a pool of fel sludge, past a group of s and .\nUpon killing Zalinor, the &lt;a href=\"Legion%20Keystone\"&gt;Legion Keystone&lt;/a&gt; will appear next to his corpse. Interact with it to proceed to the next stage.\nStage 6: Back to the Prisoner.\nHead back to the building and release Dagnar.\nStage 7: Sieging the Citadel.\nDagnar equips the &lt;a href=\"fel%20lord\"&gt;fel lord&lt;/a&gt; axe behind him and follows Sliver and the player as they run up the path to the southeast. Sliver pauses in front of an area scorched by \"Fel Creep\", which deals heavy Fire damage to characters who stand in it and slows their movement speed by 65%.\nDagnar runs across the scorched area and is burned by the fire.\nSliver instead uses &lt;a href=\"Anti-Magic%20Shell\"&gt;Anti-Magic Shell&lt;/a&gt; before crossing.\nFollow Sliver's example or use &lt;a href=\"Wraith%20Walk\"&gt;Wraith Walk&lt;/a&gt; to avoid taking damage as you pass over the scorched area.\nFight your way up to the barrier.\nSimilar to before, a Felguard Sentry and two Niskaran Doombringers emerge from the building to the east. After defeating them, another Doombringer accompanied by a and two s appear from the west.\nAfter defeating them, the next stage begins.\nStage 8: Into the Depths.\nThe area between the disabled barrier and the citadel is inhabited by Felguard Sentries, Niskaran Houndmasters and Niskaran Doombringers, as well as a large amount of s. The tumors spew fel energy around them that pushes back anyone who attempts to walk into it; using a ranged attack like &lt;a href=\"Death%27s%20Caress\"&gt;Death's Caress&lt;/a&gt; or pulling them away with &lt;a href=\"Death%20Grip\"&gt;Death Grip&lt;/a&gt; will cause them to stop spreading fel.\nJust before reaching Margrave, there is another area scorched by Fel Creep. Note that using &lt;a href=\"Anti-Magic%20Shell\"&gt;Anti-Magic Shell&lt;/a&gt; in this area will not prevent you from being slowed, so it is advisable to use &lt;a href=\"Wraith%20Walk\"&gt;Wraith Walk&lt;/a&gt; instead.\nUpon reaching the center of the complex, a short cutscene plays, showing Margrave tied to a rock pillar as Gorelix appears on the rise behind him.\nStage 9: The Fleshripper.\nGorelix regularly casts Earthshattering Slash, which deals damage to enemies directly in front of him. He also spawns large amounts of from the surrounding lava pools. Note that killing a Fel Slime will cause it to create a patch of slime that periodically inflicts Fire damage when stood in.\nUpon killing Gorelix, the Maw of the Damned falls to the ground and lands in Margrave's corpse.\nFinal Stage: The Call of Icecrown.\nWhile Sliver walks into the gate immediately, Dagnar instead walks over and briefly kneels next to Margrave's body before crossing.\nUpon using the Death Gate, you automatically exit the scenario and is transported to the &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Throne\"&gt;Frozen Throne&lt;/a&gt;.\nYou receive the &lt;a href=\"http%3A//www.wowhead.com/spell%3D190652/mark-of-the-lich-king\"&gt;Mark of the Lich King&lt;/a&gt; buff, increasing all of your stats by 5% for 60 minutes.\nAn Acherus Waygate opens to the immediate right of the Lich King. Use it to travel to and speak with &lt;a href=\"Darion%20Mograine\"&gt;Darion Mograine&lt;/a&gt; in the center to complete the quest.\nBeta version.\nTravel to the Broken Shore and travel through the Demon Portal, find Baron Sliver, and obtain the Maw of the Damned."}
{"id": "492316", "revid": "49740203", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=492316", "title": "The Dead and the Damned (Horde)", "text": "Objectives.\nTravel to &lt;a href=\"Dalaran\"&gt;Dalaran&lt;/a&gt; and fly upon &lt;a href=\"Zeomus\"&gt;Zeomus&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Darkstone%20Isle\"&gt;Darkstone Isle&lt;/a&gt;. While there, travel through the Demon Portal, find &lt;a href=\"Baron%20Sliver\"&gt;Baron Sliver&lt;/a&gt;, and obtain the &lt;a href=\"Maw%20of%20the%20Damned\"&gt;Maw of the Damned&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\n&lt;A powerful mind again touches your thoughts.&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Gorelix%20the%20Fleshripper\"&gt;Gorelix the Fleshripper&lt;/a&gt; is a monstrous demon. The butcher of a thousand worlds, he has exterminated countless races with his axe, the Maw of the Damned.\nA group of &lt;a href=\"Knights%20of%20the%20Ebon%20Blade\"&gt;Ebon Blade&lt;/a&gt; was dispatched to slay him but they have gone missing. You will succeed where they failed.\nYou will not be alone in this, I've sent Baron Sliver ahead to assist you.\nGo, obtain the Maw of the Damned and ensure that Gorelix is no more.\nCompletion.\nThat axe makes me feel uneasy, &lt;name&gt;. Its power is undeniable, but its very essence embodies the &lt;a href=\"eternal%20hunger\"&gt;eternal hunger&lt;/a&gt;.\nWe will use it because we must do whatever it takes to win this war. Still, I'd be careful with that weapon if I were you.\nNotes.\nUpon mounting Zeomus, you are transported to &lt;a href=\"Darkstone%20Isle\"&gt;Darkstone Isle&lt;/a&gt; on the western side of the Broken Shore where several Knights of the Ebon Blade are stationed. &lt;a href=\"Vanessa%20Fairgraves\"&gt;Vanessa Fairgraves&lt;/a&gt; is standing nearby and salutes you as you walk past.\n&lt;a href=\"Rantuko%20Grimtouch\"&gt;Rantuko Grimtouch&lt;/a&gt; is standing in front of the demon portal.\nUpon walking through the portal, you are transported to &lt;a href=\"Niskara\"&gt;Niskara&lt;/a&gt;.\nStage 1: Hunting the Hunters.\nSliver is found just up the path, having been shackled by a .\nUpon killing the jailer, Sliver is freed.\nStage 2: Scout the Path.\nKill the two and then proceed east.\nStage 3: Breaching the Defenses.\nA Felguard Sentry and emerge from a building to the north. Kill them both to proceed to the next stage.\nStage 4: The Search Continues.\nFollow Sliver east into the Legion camp and kill the Felguard Sentries patrolling the path.\nInside one of the buildings, &lt;a href=\"Minerva%20Ravensorrow\"&gt;Minerva Ravensorrow&lt;/a&gt; has been strung up with fel shackles.\nStage 5: End of the Inquisition.\nZalinor is found to the northeast overlooking a pool of fel sludge, past a group of s and .\nUpon killing Zalinor, the &lt;a href=\"Legion%20Keystone\"&gt;Legion Keystone&lt;/a&gt; will appear next to his corpse. Interact with it to proceed to the next stage.\nStage 6: Back to the Prisoner.\nHead back to the building and release Minerva.\nStage 7: Sieging the Citadel.\nMinerva equips the &lt;a href=\"fel%20lord\"&gt;fel lord&lt;/a&gt; axe behind her and follows Sliver and the player as they run up the path to the southeast. Sliver pauses in front of an area scorched by \"Fel Creep\", which deals heavy Fire damage to characters who stand in it and slows their movement speed by 65%.\nMinerva runs across the scorched area and is burned by the fire.\nSliver instead uses &lt;a href=\"Anti-Magic%20Shell\"&gt;Anti-Magic Shell&lt;/a&gt; before crossing.\nFollow Sliver's example or use &lt;a href=\"Wraith%20Walk\"&gt;Wraith Walk&lt;/a&gt; to avoid taking damage as you pass over the scorched area.\nFight your way up to the barrier.\nSimilar to before, a Felguard Sentry and two Niskaran Doombringers emerge from the building to the east. After defeating them, another Doombringer accompanied by a and two s appear from the west.\nAfter defeating them, the next stage begins.\nStage 8: Into the Depths.\nThe area between the disabled barrier and the citadel is inhabited by Felguard Sentries, Niskaran Houndmasters and Niskaran Doombringers, as well as a large amount of s. The tumors spew fel energy around them that pushes back anyone who attempts to walk into it; using a ranged attack like &lt;a href=\"Death%27s%20Caress\"&gt;Death's Caress&lt;/a&gt; or pulling them away with &lt;a href=\"Death%20Grip\"&gt;Death Grip&lt;/a&gt; will cause them to stop spreading fel.\nJust before reaching Margrave, there is another area scorched by Fel Creep. Note that using &lt;a href=\"Anti-Magic%20Shell\"&gt;Anti-Magic Shell&lt;/a&gt; in this area will not prevent you from being slowed, so it is advisable to use &lt;a href=\"Wraith%20Walk\"&gt;Wraith Walk&lt;/a&gt; instead.\nUpon reaching the center of the complex, a short cutscene plays, showing Margrave tied to a rock pillar as Gorelix appears on the rise behind him.\nStage 9: The Fleshripper.\nGorelix regularly casts Earthshattering Slash, which deals damage to enemies directly in front of him. He also spawns large amounts of from the surrounding lava pools. Note that killing a Fel Slime will cause it to create a patch of slime that periodically inflicts Fire damage when stood in.\nUpon killing Gorelix, the Maw of the Damned falls to the ground and lands in Margrave's corpse.\nFinal Stage: The Call of Icecrown.\nWhile Sliver walks into the gate immediately, Minerva instead walks over and briefly kneels next to Margrave's body before crossing.\nUpon using the Death Gate, you automatically exit the scenario and is transported to the &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Throne\"&gt;Frozen Throne&lt;/a&gt;.\nYou receive the &lt;a href=\"http%3A//www.wowhead.com/spell%3D190652/mark-of-the-lich-king\"&gt;Mark of the Lich King&lt;/a&gt; buff, increasing all of your stats by 5% for 60 minutes.\nAn Acherus Waygate opens to the immediate right of the Lich King. Use it to travel to and speak with &lt;a href=\"Darion%20Mograine\"&gt;Darion Mograine&lt;/a&gt; in the center to complete the quest.\nIn case the Maw of the Damned is not your first choice, you are teleported from the Niskara directly to Acherus. Upon completion, no speech occurs.\nBeta version.\nTravel to the Broken Shore and travel through the Demon Portal, find Baron Sliver, and obtain the Maw of the Damned."}
