{"id": "403319", "revid": "49723770", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=403319", "title": "The Defense of Karabor", "text": "Objectives.\nDestroy the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Horde\"&gt;Iron Horde&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Karabor\"&gt;Karabor&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nDefend Karabor from the Iron Horde.\nAt the end of the northern courtyard is &lt;a href=\"Arnokk%20the%20Burner\"&gt;Arnokk the Burner&lt;/a&gt;. He guards the entrance to the harbor behind Karabor, where the main Iron Horde army is waiting.\nOnce we've taken care of him, we'll need to deal with the Iron Horde leader, &lt;a href=\"Commander%20Vorka\"&gt;Commander Vorka&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"On accept:\"\nRewards.\nYou will receive one of:\nYou will also receive:\nProgress.\nAs this scenario can only be done once, it is documented here.\nStage 1: Defeat Arnokk the Burner.\nHead south. Arnokk at the eastern end of the courtyard near the door to the south. Save cooldowns for the last 20% when he summons reinforcements -- they will despawn on his death.\nStage 2: Meet Yrel at the Karabor Harbor.\nAfter Arnokk's death, keep moving south and kill five orcs along the way. Be warned that once you exit the hallway, &lt;a href=\"Commander%20Vorka\"&gt;Commander Vorka&lt;/a&gt; will order the fleet to constantly bombard the stairs. Head through the hall and down the stairs to the southeast. Yrel is at the base of the steps.\nClearing the trios of orcs will free up the defenders and they will throw you a heal \nbefore leaving.\nStage 3: Protect K'ara from the invading forces.\nStart killing the waves of attackers. At 66%:\nKeep killing. K'ara will help by zapping enemies nearby.\nFinal Stage: Kill Commmander Vorka!\nFinish off the last of the spawned adds. Vorka is just to the east. Aggro him:\nFire Support: Black Skies\nFinish him off.\nFinale.\nHop on Raindash to fly back to &lt;a href=\"Embaari%20Village\"&gt;Embaari Village&lt;/a&gt; to turn in to Yrel.\n\"On exiting scenario at Embaari Village:\"\nCompletion.\nWe did it, &lt;name&gt;. Without your heroic efforts, the Temple of Karabor would have been lost to the Iron Horde.\nProphet Velen would be proud of us.\nNotes.\nThis completes the \"The Light Prevails\" portion of &lt;a href=\"As%20I%20Walk%20Through%20the%20Valley%20of%20the%20Shadow%20of%20Moon\"&gt;As I Walk Through the Valley of the Shadow of Moon&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Gorgrond%20storyline\"&gt;Gorgrond storyline&lt;/a&gt; begins with &lt;a href=\"The%20Secrets%20of%20Gorgrond%20%28Alliance%29\"&gt;The Secrets of Gorgrond (Alliance)&lt;/a&gt;, which opened up as soon as players reached level 92.\nYrel will later mail the player &lt;a href=\"The%20Prophet%27s%20Arcanum\"&gt;The Prophet's Arcanum&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe achievement also unlocks the purchase of the &lt;a href=\"Shadowmoon%20Valley%20Treasure%20Map\"&gt;Shadowmoon Valley Treasure Map&lt;/a&gt;, to which Grakis will also send the player a letter."}
