{"id": "565713", "revid": "3154973", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=565713", "title": "A Good War", "text": "A Good War is a \"&lt;a href=\"World%20of%20Warcraft\"&gt;World of Warcraft&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"novella\"&gt;novella&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=\"Robert%20Brooks\"&gt;Robert Brooks&lt;/a&gt;. It recounts the &lt;a href=\"War%20of%20the%20Thorns\"&gt;War of the Thorns&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt;'s point of view, while its companion novella \"&lt;a href=\"Elegy\"&gt;Elegy&lt;/a&gt;\" details the &lt;a href=\"Alliance\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt; perspective. Both novellas take place simultaneously. The story takes place after the events of \"&lt;a href=\"Before%20the%20Storm\"&gt;Before the Storm&lt;/a&gt;\".\nA limited edition hardback book containing both \"A Good War\" and \"Elegy\" along with exclusive original artwork will be included in the \"\". Both stories were announced to become available online later in 2018, but buying the Collector's Edition would remain the only way to own the hardback version containing original artwork. The &lt;a href=\"Digital%20books\"&gt;digital version&lt;/a&gt; of the stories was released on August 6, 2018."}
