{"id": "46706", "revid": "40389549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46706", "title": "Into The Scarlet Monastery (Classic)", "text": "Objectives.\nKill High Inquisitor Whitemane, Scarlet Commander Mograine, Herod, the Scarlet Champion and Houndmaster Loksey and then report back to &lt;a href=\"Varimathras\"&gt;Varimathras&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Undercity\"&gt;Undercity&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nWhilst the &lt;a href=\"Sylvanas%20Windrunner\"&gt;Dark Lady&lt;/a&gt; tends to the pressing issue of the &lt;a href=\"Lich%20King\"&gt;Lich King&lt;/a&gt;'s advance to the north, I am seeing to it that matters closer to home are being taken care of accordingly.\nNo doubt, the &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; pests who call themselves the &lt;a href=\"Scarlet%20Crusade\"&gt;Scarlet Crusade&lt;/a&gt; are proving to be the sharpest thorn in our side domestically. &lt;a href=\"Tirisfal%20Glades\"&gt;Tirisfal Glades&lt;/a&gt; is literally crawling with the little red ants.\nTravel to the &lt;a href=\"Scarlet%20Monastery\"&gt;Monastery&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;class&gt;, and lay waste to High Inquisitor Whitemane and her top lieutenants.\nProgress.\nPerhaps I was not explicit in my orders, &lt;class&gt;. I want High Inquisitor Whitemane killed once and for all. And while you're at it, take out her top brass as well.\nKill that zealot, Scarlet Commander Mograine. Lay waste to Herod, the Scarlet Champion. And slaughter Houndmaster Loksey and his filthy mutts too.\nNow begone!\nCompletion.\nYou have served the Dark Lady well, &lt;class&gt;. 'Twas no small task I asked of you.\nYour loyalty to the &lt;a href=\"Forsaken\"&gt;Forsaken&lt;/a&gt; has been noted. And your tenacity in combat will be remembered.\nNotes.\nThis quest takes place in the library (Houndmaster Loksey), Armory (Herod), and Cathedral (Scarlet Commander Mograine and High Inquistitor Whitemane). You can complete this quest without even running the graveyard. You will likely complete this quest as you level, accomplishing it around level 36-37, so don't worry about completing it all at once, and don't expect to be able to run all four instances with a graveyard level group."}
{"id": "45699", "revid": "49848256", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45699", "title": "Into The Temple of Atal'Hakkar", "text": "Objectives.\nGather 10 Atal'ai Tablets for &lt;a href=\"Brohann%20Caskbelly\"&gt;Brohann Caskbelly&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Stormwind\"&gt;Stormwind&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nAccording to legend, The &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Atal%27Hakkar\"&gt;Temple of Atal'Hakkar&lt;/a&gt; is a holy shrine dedicated to the ancient god, &lt;a href=\"Hakkar%20the%20Soulflayer\"&gt;Hakkar the Soulflayer&lt;/a&gt;. Maintained by a vicious tribe of trolls named the &lt;a href=\"Atal%27ai\"&gt;Atal'ai&lt;/a&gt;, the temple is rumored to be impenetrable.\nNow sunk beneath the &lt;a href=\"Pool%20of%20Tears\"&gt;Pool of Tears&lt;/a&gt;, retrieving artifacts from the temple is even more difficult. But that's what I need you to do, &lt;name&gt;.\nAid me by gathering the intact Atal'ai Tablets. Bring them to me and I will return to the &lt;a href=\"Explorers%27%20Guild\"&gt;Explorers' Guild&lt;/a&gt; a hero. Together we will share the glory.\nRewards.\nYou will receive: &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20Talisman\"&gt;Guardian Talisman&lt;/a&gt;\nProgress.\nAs dusk slowly descends upon my career I turn to you, &lt;name&gt;, to help me in my final quest for the Explorers' League. If my old bones could muster the strength to brave the &lt;a href=\"Swamp%20of%20Sorrows\"&gt;Swamp of Sorrows&lt;/a&gt; and the sunken temple I would be fighting right alongside you.\nPride makes it hard for me to ask for your help in collecting the Atal'ai Tablets. But old age forces the necessity.\nPlease help me, &lt;name&gt;. I want to retire from the Explorers' League having completed their final bidding.\nCompletion.\nThe Atal'ai Tablets! Thank you, &lt;name&gt;!\nOnce I deliver these to the Explorers' League our names shall go down in history together. You have helped an old dwarf fulfill his final obligation in life. For that I am eternally grateful.\nNotes.\nWhile there are other tablets in the temple, there are two which don't require you to kill any of the elites in the temple. Enter the temple and you'll have to dive under the water. When you emerge, you'll be in a wide hall, \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Broken%20Hall\"&gt;The Broken Hall&lt;/a&gt;\". Out of the water, there will be one tablet on the right. There is also one tablet under water. The respawn time on the tablets is about 7.5 minutes, so you can complete the quest in 30 minutes if you just wait for the respawns."}
