{"id": "76407", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=76407", "title": "Into the Breach (Blasted Lands)", "text": "Objectives.\nKill 6 &lt;a href=\"Invading%20Felguard\"&gt;Invading Felguard&lt;/a&gt;s and then return to &lt;a href=\"Agent%20Proudwell\"&gt;Argent Emissary Proudwell&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nBattle rages non-stop at the portal! The Argent Dawn is fighting a desperate fight\u2014and if we lose, then there will be no end to the demon's fire.\nHelp us, &lt;name&gt;. Enter the breach and lend aid to our brothers and sisters. Help stem this tide of darkness! The &lt;a href=\"Argent%20Dawn\"&gt;Argent Dawn&lt;/a&gt; -- and the world\u2014needs you! \nProgress.\nOnce again into the breach, my friend!\nCompletion.\nThank you, &lt;name&gt;. Among the chaos of battle, heroes burn bright against the darkness. Your light shines true!\nHistory.\nThis quest was a bit of a pain at the time for a lone &lt;a href=\"melee\"&gt;melee&lt;/a&gt; class player, because \"all\" of the Invading Felguards came out of the Dark Portal - a rather small door. Classes with &lt;a href=\"Area%20of%20Effect\"&gt;Area of Effect&lt;/a&gt; spells would target the portal, tagging all of the invading forces for themselves or their party before a melee character could even get a hit in. Many melee players had to join groups to complete the quest. This quest, like many things in \"The &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Crusade\"&gt;Burning Crusade&lt;/a&gt;\" Expansion that this quest preceded, was a learning experience for &lt;a href=\"Blizzard%20Entertainment\"&gt;Blizzard Entertainment&lt;/a&gt;, and lead to considerations for future quests where there was the potential for many players to do at the same time."}
{"id": "186207", "revid": "22514", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=186207", "title": "Into the Breach (Grizzly Hills)", "text": "Objectives.\n&lt;a href=\"Kurun\"&gt;Kurun&lt;/a&gt; on the hill overlooking &lt;a href=\"Thor%20Modan\"&gt;Thor Modan&lt;/a&gt; wants you to kill &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Thane%20Argrum\"&gt;Iron Thane Argrum&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nIf we can't overcome the defenders inside Thor Modan, the iron dwarves can hold out forever. The &lt;a href=\"Earthen\"&gt;Earthen&lt;/a&gt; are bravely taking on the constructs built by the sons of iron, but they cannot break into the city.\nThe tunnels narrow too quickly for my fellow giants to be of use, so our options are few. Would you be willing to venture into the city and kill the dwarf commanding the resistance? \nRewards.\nYou will be able to choose one of these rewards:\nYou will also receive: \nProgress.\nWere you able to kill the commander?\nCompletion.\nWell done, &lt;name&gt;. The loss of the iron dwarf commander should be enough to break the remaining defenders. The Earthen should be able to deal with the survivors.\nNotes.\nThe Iron Thane is near the (NE) end of the trench. If you cannot fly and don't want to wade through all the mobs (possibly \"again\") to get to the thane, you could climb onto any of the middle pillars and jump into the water. There are also some (many?) spots where a fall is not necessarily fatal.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Runic%20Prophecies\"&gt;The Runic Prophecies&lt;/a&gt; is another quest that sends you deep into Thor Modan, and can usefully be done at the same time as this one.\nThe Alliance quest chain starting with &lt;a href=\"Softening%20the%20Blow\"&gt;Softening the Blow&lt;/a&gt; also sends the character into Thor Modan."}
{"id": "361255", "revid": "49740203", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=361255", "title": "Into the Brewery", "text": "Into the Brewery is an optional dungeon lead-in quest for Stormstout Brewery.\nObjectives.\nSpeak to &lt;a href=\"Chen%20Stormstout\"&gt;Chen Stormstout&lt;/a&gt; inside the &lt;a href=\"Stormstout%20Brewery\"&gt;Stormstout Brewery&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nWe need to find out what's going on inside that brewery, &lt;name&gt;!\nWe may have cleared out some of the bigger pests, but I'm certain there's plenty more where they came from. Gather up a few of your friends, and meet me inside! \nRewards.\nYou will receive: (or at lvl 90)\nCompletion.\nYou came! Great!\nI'm looking forward to fighting by your side again, &lt;name&gt;.\nNotes.\nAs with nearly all dungeon quest givers, Chen will be standing by the entrance of the instance. There is a scripted speech event when you enter, so you may wish to enter now to listen to it at your leisure, rather than inconvenience an impatient dungeon group."}
